  "text": "The urothelium may play a role in the mechanosensory transduction during voiding via its ability to release many substances in response to stretch during filling, including ATP [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , prostaglandins [CITATION_3] , nitric oxide [CITATION_4] , acetylcholine [CITATION_5] and nerve growth factor [CITATION_6] , which affect nerve, smooth muscle, interstitial and immune cells.",
